# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# dudoxx-ai-terminal — .env.example
#
# Copy to `.env` (project-local) or `~/.ddx-term/.env` (global, all clients) to
# override the built-in defaults. EVERY value here is optional — with no .env at
# all the stack runs on the 133XX defaults below.
#
# Precedence (HIGHEST wins, override:false everywhere):
#   1. The MCP client's `env:` block in .mcp.json / `claude mcp add --env`  (per-client)
#   2. This project-local `.env` (current working directory)
#   3. Global `~/.ddx-term/.env`  (every client on the machine)
#   4. Built-in code defaults (the values shown below)
#
# Loaded by: ddx-term-mcp (src/load-dotenv.ts), and — for the standalone
# `pnpm dev` path — by the broker (src/main.ts) and web (server.mjs) directly.
# Dudoxx UG / Acceleate Consulting - Walid Boudabbous <walid@acceleate.com>
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Ports (133XX band — chosen to avoid colliding with your own dev servers) ──
# Broker HTTP/WS port (NestJS).
DDX_TERM_BROKER_PORT=13330
# Web UI HTTP port (Next.js).
DDX_TERM_WEB_PORT=13340
# Bind/connect host for broker + web. Loopback-only by design (v1 has no auth).
DDX_TERM_HOST=127.0.0.1

# ── tmux shared session ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# tmux -S socket path of the shared session.
DDX_TERM_SOCKET=/tmp/ddx-term.sock
# Session name hosting all terminals (one tmux window per terminalId).
DDX_TERM_SESSION=ddx-shared

# ── MCP agent-channel behaviour ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# terminalId used when a verb omits `terminalId`.
DDX_TERM_DEFAULT=t01
# Hard cap on scrollback lines returned per term_read call.
DDX_TERM_MAX_READ_LINES=2000
# Max terminals the agent may allocate.
DDX_TERM_MAX_TERMINALS=16
# Optional command allow-list (path to a newline-delimited file). Unset = no allow-list.
# DDX_TERM_ALLOWLIST=

# ── Supervisor (MCP auto-spawn of broker + web) ───────────────────────────────
# Set to 0 to run broker-only (headless) — the MCP will NOT spawn the web UI.
# DDX_TERM_WEB=0

# DDX_TERM_BROKER_URL / DDX_TERM_BROKER_WS / BROKER_BASE_URL are written
# automatically by the supervisor after it spawns the broker — do NOT set them by
# hand unless you are pointing the MCP at an already-running broker. If you do,
# DDX_TERM_BROKER_URL MUST include the /api/v1 prefix or registry resolution
# fails silently, e.g.:
# DDX_TERM_BROKER_URL=http://127.0.0.1:13330/api/v1
